#. Tag: title
#: zseries_rescue_initrd.xml:18
#, no-c-format
msgid "IBM &zseries;: Using initrd as a Rescue System"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: dm:docmanager
#: zseries_rescue_initrd.xml:21
#, no-c-format
msgid "<dm:bugtracker></dm:bugtracker> <dm:translation>yes</dm:translation>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: zseries_rescue_initrd.xml:27
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the kernel of the &slsreg; for IBM &zseries; is upgraded or modified, it "
"is possible to reboot the system accidentally in an inconsistent state, so "
"standard procedures of IPLing the installed system fail. In such a case, you "
"may use the installation system for rescue purposes."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: zseries_rescue_initrd.xml:34
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"IPL the &sls; for IBM &zseries; installation system as described in <xref "
"linkend=\"sec.zseries.prep\"/>. Choose <guimenu>Start Installation</guimenu> "
"and enter all required parameters. After the installation system has loaded "
"and you are asked which display type to use to control the installation, "
"select <literal>SSH</literal>. Now you can log in to the system with SSH as "
"&rootuser; without a password."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: zseries_rescue_initrd.xml:43
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In this state, no disks are configured. You need to configure them before "
"you can proceed."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: zseries_rescue_initrd.xml:49
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring DASDs"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: zseries_rescue_initrd.xml:51
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configure DASDs with the following command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: zseries_rescue_initrd.xml:54
#, no-c-format
msgid "dasd_configure 0.0.0150 1 0"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: zseries_rescue_initrd.xml:55
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"0.0.0150 is the channel to which the DASD is connected. The <literal>1</"
"literal> means activate the disk (a <literal>0</literal> at this place would "
"deactivate the disk). The <literal>0</literal> stands for <quote>no DIAG "
"mode</quote> for the disk (a <literal>1</literal> here would enable DAIG "
"access to the disk)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: zseries_rescue_initrd.xml:64
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Now the DASD is online (check with <command>cat /proc/partitions</command>) "
"and can used for subsequent commands."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: zseries_rescue_initrd.xml:72
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring a zFCP Disk"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: zseries_rescue_initrd.xml:74
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To configure a zFCP disk, it is necessary to first configure the zFCP "
"adapter. Do this with the following command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: zseries_rescue_initrd.xml:78
#, no-c-format
msgid "zfcp_host_configure 0.0.4000 1"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: zseries_rescue_initrd.xml:79
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>0.0.4000</literal> is the channel to which the adapter is attached "
"and <literal>1</literal> stands for activate (a <literal>0</literal> here "
"would deactivate the adapter)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: zseries_rescue_initrd.xml:86
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After the adapter is activated, a disk can be configured. Do this with the "
"following command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: zseries_rescue_initrd.xml:90
#, no-c-format
msgid "zfcp_disk_configure 0.0.4000 1234567887654321 8765432100000000  1"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: zseries_rescue_initrd.xml:91
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>0.0.4000</literal> is the previously-used channel ID, "
"<literal>1234567887654321</literal> is the WWPN (World wide Port Number), "
"and <literal>8765432100000000</literal> is the LUN (logical unit number). "
"The <literal>1</literal> stands for activating the disk (a <literal>0</"
"literal> here would deactivate the disk)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: zseries_rescue_initrd.xml:100
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Now the zFCP disk is online (check with <command>cat /proc/partitions</"
"command>) and can used for subsequent commands."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: zseries_rescue_initrd.xml:107
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Now the rescue system is fully set up and you can start repairing the "
"installed system. See <xref linkend=\"sec.trouble.data.recover.rescue\"/> "
"for instructions on how to repair the most common issues."
msgstr ""
